# Design System Enforcer (auto)

**Users should not need slash commands.** Map natural language to skills yourself.

## Intent → load (mandatory)

| User intent (examples) | Load skills in order |
|------------------------|----------------------|
| Build/change UI, page, screen, component, form, layout, styling | `frontend-judgment` (if non-trivial) → `design-tokens` → `ui-components` → `anti-ai-slop` → `accessibility` |
| Animation / transition / motion | above + `motion` |
| Design audit, AI slop, "UI jelek/generik", visual review | `anti-ai-slop` → `design-tokens` → `accessibility` → `web-performance` (+ judgment if proposing redesign directions) |
| Tests / TDD / coverage / regresi UI | `frontend-testing` → `ui-components` → `accessibility` |
| Slow UI / LCP / optimize performance | `web-performance` (+ `ui-components` if touching UI) |

## Expert judgment

For blank-canvas or ambiguous UI: offer **2–3 approaches + tradeoffs + one recommendation** before coding. Skip for tiny clear fixes or “just implement”. See skill `frontend-judgment`.

## Rules

- Prefer project design system if one exists; otherwise `tokens/*.css`
- No raw hex, purple/indigo defaults, Lorem ipsum, or `rounded-2xl` everywhere
- Handle loading / error / empty; keyboard accessible
- Optional shortcuts only: `/ui`, `/design`, `/test-ui` — never require them
- Audits: do not fabricate visual metrics without tokens/screenshots (design-reviewer honesty)
